dismissalComment.html: castled! Full and angled into the stumps. Campher, knowing that third man is up, tries the reverse ramp. commentPreTextItems.html: Prem: "What a cracker from both these teams, No matter who wins both of teams can be proud of the character shown in this game "

commentTextItems.html: Scotland HAVE DONE IT! The luck of the Irish rubs off on Leask instead, whose inside edge runs away to the boundary! There will be bagpipes in Bulawayo tonight!

commentPostTextItems.html: Leask celebrates, unadulterated joy on his face, while the devastation on Ireland's is plain to see. This is huge for Scotland, not just for World Cup chances, but just the exhilaration of winning a match like that. Ireland will feel they've given this one away, and watched their World Cup hopes go up in smoke.

"We've had a few tough games against Ireland, so to get this against them is even more special" Leask says. "Watt played an absolute blinder of an innings too. We've got a great bunch of lads and this is just the start of our journey. This is how we'll play our cricket, we'll take things deep."
Prem: "King Charles , Please declare knighthood to Leask!!!!! He deserves it , for putting Scotland on the cricketing map!!'
Kenneth: "Michael Leask, the Scott McTominay and John McGinn of Scottish cricket!!"
There's a shout-out for Brandon McMullen too, who he calls "an absolute hero". Unsurprisingly named player of the match.

"The first ten overs when we were batting and the last ten overs when we were bowling took the game away from us," Balbirnie pithily sums up. "We'll lick our wounds here and go again next game. The plans were pretty clear and I can't be too critical of the bowlers, but I can't fault the bowlers too much. It's an uphill battle from here But I back our guys to be up to the mark"

"It's all the sweeter against Ireland," says Richie Berrington. "Absolutely delighted ti start things off with a win. We've had a good couple of weeks leading into this in South Africa coming into Zim. We'll look to keep building on this.

"It was very tense towards the end. Games like that keep you on the edge of their seat. I don't think we could have asked for a better start with the ball. McMullen was outstanding and I think he'll keep getting better. Wasn't feeling too great at one point but managed to get back onto the field." That might explain why he didn't bowl ten overs.
That's it from us here, see you again tomorrow!

seriesStandings.notes:
In the event of teams finishing on equal points in their Group
a) The team with the greatest number of wins in its Group will be placed in the higher position.
b) If there are teams with equal points and equal wins in the Group stage, then in such case the team with the higher net run rate in the Group stage will be placed in the higher position
c) If two or more teams are still equal, they will be ordered according to the head to head match played between them (points then net run rate in those matches).
d) If the above does not resolve the Group ordering, or if all matches within a Group produce no results, then any tied teams will be ordered as per their original Group Stage seedings and the top 3 teams in each Group will progress to the Super Six stage.
In the event of teams finishing on equal points in the Super Six stage a) The team with the greatest number of wins in all of the matches throughout the competition against the other Super Six stage qualifiers will be placed in the higher position.
b) If there are teams with equal points and equal wins in the Super Six stage, then in such case the team with the higher net run rate in all matches played against the other Super Six qualifiers will be placed in the higher position
c) If two or more teams are still equal, they will be ordered according to the head-to-head match(es) played between them (points then net run rate in those matches).
d) If still equal, any teams that cannot be separated in this way shall be placed according to their original Group seeding.
e) If the above does not resolve the Super Six stage ordering, or if all matches within the Super Six stage produce no results, then the order of finishing will be determined by the team's performances in the Group stage as follows: Group standing, most points, most wins. If still equal, any teams that cannot be separated in this way shall be placed according to their original Group ranking.
